  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Network Security Engineer",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities:</p><ul><li>Oversees projects management and implementation.</li><li>Codify implementation design into documented for end user's record.</li><li>Conduct training and presentation for team members and end-users.</li><li>Provide technical testing or support to pre-sales engineer/customer on the network setup.</li><li>Assist in technical communications with customer/partner, to ensure closure of sales order.</li><li>Ensuring that the solution can deliver on to the customer’s requirements.</li><li>Work closely with Level 2 support, if case issue is escalated to Level 3.</li><li>Maintain rapport with customers and competence in managing vendors.</li><li>Any other ad-hoc duties assigned.</li></ul><p>Requirements:</p><ul><li>Degree/Diploma in IT Networking or equivalent</li><li>At least 2 years of work experience in a SI or distributor environment with network security skillset</li><li>Good IT knowledge in OSI 7 Layer, TCP/IP, LAN/WAN technologies and network security</li><li>Ability to work under pressure with minimal supervision</li><li>Excellent in communication and analytical skill</li><li>Experience in network security projects implementation</li><li>Positive working attitude and a good team player</li><li>Willing to work extended office hours and after office hours when needed</li><li>Exposure to security solution such as Firewall, local balancer or endpoint protection will be an added advantage</li></ul><p>Interested candidates may send their CV to MAC (Reg No. R1221300) at anc1@anchorsearchgroup.com quoting the job title in the Subject line. We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>",
